place.name: TIDMINGTON
place.gazetteerText: TIDMINGTON, a parish in the district of Shipston-on-Stour, and county of Warwick; 5¼ miles NE of Moreton r. station. Post town, Shipston-on-Stour. Acres, 754. Real property, £1,614. Pop., 69. Houses, 12. The living is a rectory, annexed to Shipston-on-Stour. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
